					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>159 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>240</height>
										<width>178</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>144</height>
										<width>110</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>159 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>15 quires of 10 leaves each and 1 quire of 8 leaves at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="24 26" writtenLines="24 26">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words are written in larger characters. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Last line of text written outside ruling.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive and square script, punctuated, of the 13th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="scribe">Avraham</name>(?): perhaps the same scribe who also wrote MS Parma Palatina 2884, for the same patron in Bologna ca. 1400. Both manuscripts are festival prayer books, written in a similar style, with  two last letters of the line often very elongated.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="punctator">Yitsḥaḳ ben Shelomiyah</name>: inscribed in the colophon with a date of <date calendar="Hebrew">5057</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1397</date>), <name type="place">Cento</name>, folio 148v.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Yo᾿el ben Yitsḥaḳ</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 148v.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Uzi᾿el Mikha᾿el</name> of Camerino: inscribed, folio 1r.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Dominico Irosolomitano</name>, Italian censor (fl.1575-1614): inscribed with his name, 1597 (folio 159r); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref>, and appendix § 62-74.
</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (fl.1600-1624): inscribed with his name, 1628 (folio 158v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Machzor. Roman Use. Part II. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 26,998.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
